{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878133949,"sessionID":"ses_2856a97e0ffey48D6qOMQnb0po","part":{"id":"prt_d7a95d03c001AOhELvhRsQvbOO","messageID":"msg_d7a95bdbb001oiWBBemIMtsJ5c","sessionID":"ses_2856a97e0ffey48D6qOMQnb0po","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-0851258855004188ad10d142e39ad0a9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This design document outlines the architecture and implementation approach for the AgentRuntimeClient, a Python SDK client that provides a high-level interface for managing agents and their runtime sessions. The AgentRuntimeClient enables users to invoke agent workloads through the Router service with proper session management.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Components\n10: \n11: 1. **AgentRuntimeClient** - Main client class for agent runtime interactions\n12: 2. **AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient** - Handles HTTP communication with the Router for agent invocations\n13: 3. **Session Management Layer** - Manages session ID lifecycle (bootstrap/reuse)\n14: 4. **HTTP Client Layer** - Connection pooling and request handling via requests.Session\n15: 5. **Error Handling Layer** - Centralized exception handling\n16: 6. **Logging Layer** - Structured logging for debugging\n17: \n18: ### Design Patterns\n19: \n20: - **Context Manager Pattern** - For proper resource cleanup (`__enter__`/`__exit__`)\n21: - **Repository Pattern** - For agent runtime invocation operations\n22: - **Factory Pattern** - For creating HTTP sessions\n23: \n24: ## Package Structure\n25: \n26: The AgentRuntimeClient is part of the `agentcube-sdk` Python package:\n27: \n28: | Path | Role |\n29: |------|------|\n30: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n31: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` (main public API) |\n32: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` (HTTP layer) |\n33: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes |\n34: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` (connection pooling) |\n35: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` |\n36: \n37: ## Public API\n38: \n39: ### AgentRuntimeClient\n40: \n41: ```python\n42: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n43:     def __init__(\n44:         self,\n45:         agent_name: str,\n46:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n47:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n48:         verbose: bool = False,\n49:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n50:         timeout: int = 120,\n51:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n52:     ): ...\n53: \n54:     def __enter__(self): ...\n55:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n56: \n57:     def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n58: \n59:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n60: ```\n61: \n62: **Instance fields:**\n63: - `agent_name: str` - Name of the agent to invoke\n64: - `namespace: str` - Kubernetes namespace for the agent\n65: - `timeout: int` - Default read timeout in seconds (default: 120)\n66: - `connect_timeout: float` - Connection timeout in seconds (default: 5.0)\n67: - `logger: logging.Logger` - Logger instance\n68: - `router_url: str` - Base URL for the Router service\n69: - `session_id: Optional[str]` - Agent runtime session ID\n70: - `dp_client: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` - Data plane client\n71: \n72: ### Configuration\n73: \n74: | Component | Resolved settings |\n75: |-----------|-------------------|\n76: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL`; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` |\n77: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Same timeout defaults; base URL constructed from router_url, namespace, agent_name |\n78: \n79: ## HTTP Client Contract — Data Plane\n80: \n81: ### Base URL Construction\n82: \n83: ```text\n84: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n85: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n86: ```\n87: \n88: ### Endpoints\n89: \n90: | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n91: |--------|-----|---------|------|\n92: | `GET` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` | — |\n93: | `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n94: \n95: ### Session Bootstrap\n96: \n97: When `session_id` is not provided in `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__`:\n98: \n99: ```python\n100: # GET the base invocation URL to bootstrap session ID from response header\n101: response = session.get(base_url)\n102: session_id = response.headers.get(\"x-agentcube-session-id\")\n103: if not session_id:\n104:     raise ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")\n105: ```\n106: \n107: ### Timeout Behavior\n108: \n109: - **Connect timeout**: `connect_timeout` (default: 5.0 seconds)\n110: - **Read timeout**: `timeout` (default: 120 seconds) or per-call override\n111: - Timeout tuple: `(connect_timeout, timeout)` on each request\n112: \n113: ## Session Lifecycle\n114: \n115: ### Context Manager\n116: \n117: ```python\n118: with AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\") as client:\n119:     result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"hello\"})\n120: ```\n121: \n122: On context exit:\n123: - `close()` is called\n124: - Underlying `requests.Session` is closed\n125: \n126: ### Session ID Management\n127: \n128: **Option 1: Bootstrap (default)**\n129: ```python\n130: client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\")\n131: # Session ID is bootstrapped from Router on first use\n132: result = client.invoke(payload)\n133: ```\n134: \n135: **Option 2: Reuse existing session**\n136: ```python\n137: client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n138:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n139:     session_id=\"existing-session-id\"\n140: )\n141: # Skip bootstrap, use provided session ID\n142: result = client.invoke(payload)\n143: ```\n144: \n145: **Error handling:**\n146: - If `session_id` is falsy when `invoke` is called → `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n147: \n148: ## Error Handling\n149: \n150: ### Exception Hierarchy\n151: \n152: ```python\n153: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n154:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n155:     pass\n156: \n157: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n158:     def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n159:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n160:         self.stderr = stderr\n161:         self.command = command\n162:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n163: \n164: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n165:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n166:     pass\n167: \n168: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n169:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n170:     pass\n171: ```\n172: \n173: ### Error Scenarios\n174: \n175: | Scenario | Exception |\n176: |----------|-----------|\n177: | Router URL not provided | `ValueError` |\n178: | Session ID header missing on bootstrap | `ValueError` |\n179: | Invoke called without session ID | `ValueError` |\n180: | Network errors | `requests.exceptions.*` |\n181: | Router returns 4xx/5xx | Handled by caller (SDK returns raw response) |\n182: \n183: ## Dependencies\n184: \n185: ```toml\n186: dependencies = [\n187:     \"requests\",\n188:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n189:     \"cryptography\",\n190: ]\n191: \n192: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n193: ```\n194: \n195: ## HTTP Session Management\n196: \n197: ### Connection Pooling\n198: \n199: ```python\n200: def create_session(\n201:     pool_connections: int = 10,\n202:     pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n203: ) -> requests.Session:\n204:     \"\"\"Create a requests.Session with connection pooling.\"\"\"\n205: ```\n206: \n207: Mounts `HTTPAdapter` for both `http://` and `https://` schemes.\n208: \n209: ### Default Parameters\n210: \n211: - `pool_connections: 10`\n212: - `pool_maxsize: 10`\n213: - `timeout: 120` (read)\n214: - `connect_timeout: 5.0`\n215: \n216: ## Testing Strategy\n217: \n218: ### Unit Tests\n219: \n220: - Test session ID bootstrap logic\n221: - Test invoke method with mocked HTTP responses\n222: - Test error handling (missing session ID, missing header)\n223: - Test timeout behavior\n224: - Test context manager cleanup\n225: \n226: ### Integration Tests\n227: \n228: - Test against real Router service\n229: - Test end-to-end agent invocation workflow\n230: - Test session reuse scenarios\n231: \n232: ## Security Considerations\n233: \n234: 1. **Router Communication**: SDK does not set `Authorization` header on data plane (Router handles JWT)\n235: 2. **Input Validation**: Basic validation of required parameters\n236: 3. **Error Messages**: Avoid exposing sensitive information\n237: \n238: ## Logging\n239: \n240: Structured logging via `get_logger`:\n241: - `INFO` level by default\n242: - Can be overridden via `verbose` parameter\n243: - Logs session ID bootstrap, invoke requests, and errors\n244: \n245: ## Example Usage\n246: \n247: ### Basic invocation with session bootstrap\n248: \n249: ```python\n250: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n251: \n252: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n253:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n254:     namespace=\"default\",\n255:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n256: ) as client:\n257:     result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"What is the capital of France?\"})\n258:     print(result)\n259: ```\n260: \n261: ### Reuse existing session\n262: \n263: ```python\n264: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n265: \n266: client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n267:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n268:     session_id=\"existing-session-id\",\n269:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n270: )\n271: \n272: try:\n273:     result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"Hello\"}, timeout=60.0)\n274: finally:\n275:     client.close()\n276: ```\n277: \n278: ### Custom timeout\n279: \n280: ```python\n281: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n282:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n283:     timeout=180,  # 3 minutes\n284:     connect_timeout=10.0\n285: ) as client:\n286:     result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"Long-running task\"})\n287: ```\n288: \n289: ## Future Enhancements\n290: \n291: 1. **Async API**: Provide asynchronous versions of methods using `httpx.AsyncClient`\n292: 2. **Retry Logic**: Configurable retry with exponential backoff for transient failures\n293: 3. **Streaming**: Support streaming responses for long-running agent invocations\n294: 4. **Metrics**: Track request latency and success rates\n295: 5. **Event System**: Provide event-based API for agent lifecycle events\n\n(End of file - total 295 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis design document outlines the architecture and implementation approach for the AgentRuntimeClient, a Python SDK client that provides a high-level interface for managing agents and their runtime sessions. The AgentRuntimeClient enables users to invoke agent workloads through the Router service with proper session management.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n1. **AgentRuntimeClient** - Main client class for agent runtime interactions\n2. **AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient** - Handles HTTP communication with the Router for agent invocations\n3. **Session Management Layer** - Manages session ID lifecycle (bootstrap/reuse)\n4. **HTTP Client Layer** - Connection pooling and request handling via requests.Session\n5. **Error Handling Layer** - Centralized exception handling\n6. **Logging Layer** - Structured logging for debugging\n\n### Design Patterns\n\n- **Context Manager Pattern** - For proper resource cleanup (`__enter__`/`__exit__`)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/design.md","time":{"start":1775878133929,"end":1775878133947}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878133951,"sessionID":"ses_2856a97e0ffey48D6qOMQnb0po","part":{"id":"prt_d7a95d2fa001T51uDJW0rTXyGZ","messageID":"msg_d7a95bdbb001oiWBBemIMtsJ5c","sessionID":"ses_2856a97e0ffey48D6qOMQnb0po","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-a34497ecc42f41c398dcfbedba28e669","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Specification\n2: \n3: ## Module: sdk-python\n4: \n5: ### AgentRuntimeClient Class\n6: \n7: #### Constructor\n8: \n9: ```python\n10: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n11:     def __init__(\n12:         self,\n13:         base_url: str,\n14:         api_key: Optional[str] = None,\n15:         timeout: int = 30,\n16:         max_retries: int = 3\n17:     ) -> None\n18: ```\n19: \n20: **Parameters:**\n21: - `base_url`: Base URL of the AgentRuntime service\n22: - `api_key`: Optional API key for authentication\n23: - `timeout`: Request timeout in seconds (default: 30)\n24: - `max_retries`: Maximum number of retry attempts (default: 3)\n25: \n26: #### Agent Management Methods\n27: \n28: ##### create_agent\n29: \n30: ```python\n31: async def create_agent(\n32:     self,\n33:     config: AgentConfig,\n34:     workspace_id: Optional[str] = None\n35: ) -> Agent\n36: ```\n37: \n38: **Parameters:**\n39: - `config`: Agent configuration object\n40: - `workspace_id`: Optional workspace ID\n41: \n42: **Returns:** `Agent` object\n43: \n44: **Raises:** `AgentCreationError`, `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`, `ValidationError`\n45: \n46: ##### get_agent\n47: \n48: ```python\n49: async def get_agent(self, agent_id: str) -> Agent\n50: ```\n51: \n52: **Parameters:**\n53: - `agent_id`: ID of the agent\n54: \n55: **Returns:** `Agent` object\n56: \n57: **Raises:** `AgentNotFoundError`, `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`\n58: \n59: ##### list_agents\n60: \n61: ```python\n62: async def list_agents(\n63:     self,\n64:     workspace_id: Optional[str] = None,\n65:     status: Optional[AgentStatus] = None,\n66:     limit: int = 100,\n67:     offset: int = 0\n68: ) -> List[Agent]\n69: ```\n70: \n71: **Parameters:**\n72: - `workspace_id`: Optional workspace ID to filter by\n73: - `status`: Optional agent status to filter by\n74: - `limit`: Maximum number of agents to return (default: 100)\n75: - `offset`: Pagination offset (default: 0)\n76: \n77: **Returns:** List of `Agent` objects\n78: \n79: **Raises:** `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`\n80: \n81: ##### update_agent\n82: \n83: ```python\n84: async def update_agent(\n85:     self,\n86:     agent_id: str,\n87:     config: AgentConfig\n88: ) -> Agent\n89: ```\n90: \n91: **Parameters:**\n92: - `agent_id`: ID of the agent\n93: - `config`: Updated agent configuration\n94: \n95: **Returns:** Updated `Agent` object\n96: \n97: **Raises:** `AgentNotFoundError`, `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`, `ValidationError`\n98: \n99: ##### delete_agent\n100: \n101: ```python\n102: async def delete_agent(self, agent_id: str) -> None\n103: ```\n104: \n105: **Parameters:**\n106: - `agent_id`: ID of the agent\n107: \n108: **Raises:** `AgentNotFoundError`, `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`\n109: \n110: #### Runtime Operations Methods\n111: \n112: ##### start_agent\n113: \n114: ```python\n115: async def start_agent(\n116:     self,\n117:     agent_id: str,\n118:     input_data: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n119: ) -> RuntimeSession\n120: ```\n121: \n122: **Parameters:**\n123: - `agent_id`: ID of the agent\n124: - `input_data`: Optional input data for the agent\n125: \n126: **Returns:** `RuntimeSession` object\n127: \n128: **Raises:** `AgentNotFoundError`, `RuntimeError`, `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`\n129: \n130: ##### stop_agent\n131: \n132: ```python\n133: async def stop_agent(\n134:     self,\n135:     session_id: str,\n136:     graceful: bool = True\n137: ) -> None\n138: ```\n139: \n140: **Parameters:**\n141: - `session_id`: ID of the runtime session\n142: - `graceful`: Whether to stop gracefully (default: True)\n143: \n144: **Raises:** `SessionNotFoundError`, `RuntimeError`, `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`\n145: \n146: ##### get_session_status\n147: \n148: ```python\n149: async def get_session_status(self, session_id: str) -> RuntimeSession\n150: ```\n151: \n152: **Parameters:**\n153: - `session_id`: ID of the runtime session\n154: \n155: **Returns:** `RuntimeSession` object\n156: \n157: **Raises:** `SessionNotFoundError`, `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`\n158: \n159: ##### list_sessions\n160: \n161: ```python\n162: async def list_sessions(\n163:     self,\n164:     agent_id: Optional[str] = None,\n165:     status: Optional[SessionStatus] = None,\n166:     limit: int = 100,\n167:     offset: int = 0\n168: ) -> List[RuntimeSession]\n169: ```\n170: \n171: **Parameters:**\n172: - `agent_id`: Optional agent ID to filter by\n173: - `status`: Optional session status to filter by\n174: - `limit`: Maximum number of sessions to return (default: 100)\n175: - `offset`: Pagination offset (default: 0)\n176: \n177: **Returns:** List of `RuntimeSession` objects\n178: \n179: **Raises:** `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`\n180: \n181: ## Data Models\n182: \n183: ### Agent\n184: \n185: ```python\n186: class Agent(BaseModel):\n187:     agent_id: str\n188:     workspace_id: str\n189:     name: str\n190:     description: Optional[str]\n191:     config: AgentConfig\n192:     status: AgentStatus  # Enum: CREATING, ACTIVE, STOPPED, ERROR, DELETED\n193:     created_at: datetime\n194:     updated_at: datetime\n195:     metadata: Dict[str, str]\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ### AgentStatus\n199: \n200: ```python\n201: class AgentStatus(str, Enum):\n202:     CREATING = \"creating\"\n203:     ACTIVE = \"active\"\n204:     STOPPED = \"stopped\"\n205:     ERROR = \"error\"\n206:     DELETED = \"deleted\"\n207: ```\n208: \n209: ### AgentConfig\n210: \n211: ```python\n212: class AgentConfig(BaseModel):\n213:     runtime_config: RuntimeConfig\n214:     capabilities: List[str]\n215:     constraints: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n216:     resources: Optional[ResourceConfig] = None\n217: ```\n218: \n219: ### RuntimeConfig\n220: \n221: ```python\n222: class RuntimeConfig(BaseModel):\n223:     type: str  # e.g., \"llm\", \"function\", \"hybrid\"\n224:     model_id: str\n225:     parameters: Dict[str, Any]\n226: ```\n227: \n228: ### ResourceConfig\n229: \n230: ```python\n231: class ResourceConfig(BaseModel):\n232:     cpu: Optional[str] = None\n233:     memory: Optional[str] = None\n234:     gpu: Optional[str] = None\n235:     timeout: Optional[int] = None\n236: ```\n237: \n238: ### RuntimeSession\n239: \n240: ```python\n241: class RuntimeSession(BaseModel):\n242:     session_id: str\n243:     agent_id: str\n244:     status: SessionStatus  # Enum: STARTING, RUNNING, COMPLETED, STOPPED, ERROR\n245:     input_data: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n246:     output_data: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n247:     started_at: datetime\n248:     completed_at: Optional[datetime] = None\n249:     error_message: Optional[str] = None\n250: ```\n251: \n252: ### SessionStatus\n253: \n254: ```python\n255: class SessionStatus(str, Enum):\n256:     STARTING = \"starting\"\n257:     RUNNING = \"running\"\n258:     COMPLETED = \"completed\"\n259:     STOPPED = \"stopped\"\n260:     ERROR = \"error\"\n261: ```\n262: \n263: ## Exception Hierarchy\n264: \n265: ```\n266: AgentRuntimeException\n267: ├── AuthenticationError\n268: ├── ConnectionError\n269: ├── AgentError\n270: │   ├── AgentCreationError\n271: │   ├── AgentNotFoundError\n272: │   └── AgentUpdateError\n273: ├── RuntimeError\n274: │   ├── SessionNotFoundError\n275: │   └── RuntimeError as ExecutionError\n276: └── ValidationError\n277: ```\n278: \n279: ## HTTP Endpoints\n280: \n281: ### Agent Endpoints\n282: \n283: - `POST /v1/agents` - Create agent\n284: - `GET /v1/agents/{agent_id}` - Get agent\n285: - `GET /v1/agents` - List agents\n286: - `PUT /v1/agents/{agent_id}` - Update agent\n287: - `DELETE /v1/agents/{agent_id}` - Delete agent\n288: \n289: ### Runtime Endpoints\n290: \n291: - `POST /v1/agents/{agent_id}/start` - Start agent\n292: - `POST /v1/sessions/{session_id}/stop` - Stop agent\n293: - `GET /v1/sessions/{session_id}` - Get session status\n294: - `GET /v1/sessions` - List sessions\n\n(End of file - total 294 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Specification\n\n## Module: sdk-python\n\n### AgentRuntimeClient Class\n\n#### Constructor\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        base_url: str,\n        api_key: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 30,\n        max_retries: int = 3\n    ) -> None\n```\n\n**Parameters:**","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/spec.md","time":{"start":1775878133932,"end":1775878133949}}}}
