agent_id\n103: - [ ] Add filtering by status\n104: - [ ] Implement pagination\n105: - [ ] Write unit tests\n106: - [ ] Write integration tests\n107: \n108: ## Phase 4: Testing and Documentation (Week 7-8)\n109: \n110: ### 4.1 Unit Tests\n111: - [ ] Achieve >90% code coverage\n112: - [ ] Test all public methods\n113: - [ ] Test error handling paths\n114: - [ ] Test data model validation\n115: - [ ] Add edge case tests\n116: \n117: ### 4.2 Integration Tests\n118: - [ ] Set up test environment\n119: - [ ] Mock AgentRuntime service responses\n120: - [ ] Test end-to-end workflows\n121: - [ ] Test authentication scenarios\n122: - [ ] Test error scenarios\n123: \n124: ### 4.3 Documentation\n125: - [ ] Write module docstrings\n126: - [ ] Write class docstrings\n127: - [ ] Write method docstrings\n128: - [ ] Add parameter descriptions\n129: - [ ] Add return type descriptions\n130: - [ ] Add exception documentation\n131: - [ ] Add usage examples\n132: \n133: ### 4.4 Usage Examples\n134: - [ ] Create basic usage example\n135: - [ ] Create agent lifecycle example\n136: - [ ] Create session management example\n137: - [ ] Create error handling example\n138: - [ ] Add examples to documentation\n139: \n140: ### 4.5 Performance Testing\n141: - [ ] Benchmark common operations\n142: - [ ] Test with high concurrency\n143: - [ ] Identify bottlenecks\n144: - [ ] Optimize hot paths\n145: - [ ] Document performance characteristics\n146: \n147: ## Phase 5: Review and Release (Week 9-10)\n148: \n149: ### 5.1 Code Review\n150: - [ ] Self-review all code\n151: - [ ] Check for consistency\n152: - [ ] Verify error handling\n153: - [ ] Check type annotations\n154: - [ ] Review test coverage\n155: \n156: ### 5.2 Bug Fixes\n157: - [ ] Fix any bugs found during review\n158: - [ ] Add tests for bug fixes\n159: - [ ] Update documentation as needed\n160: \n161: ### 5.3 Release Preparation\n162: - [ ] Update CHANGE.md\n163: - [ ] Update README.md with implementation details\n164: - [ ] Verify all dependencies are correct\n165: - [ ] Check version number\n166: - [ ] Prepare release notes\n167: \n168: ### 5.4 Documentation Review\n169: - [ ] Review all documentation\n170: - [ ] Check for clarity\n171: - [ ] Verify examples work\n172: - [ ] Check for completeness\n173: - [ ] Get feedback from peers\n174: \n175: ## Additional Tasks\n176: \n177: ### Configuration\n178: - [ ] Add configuration file support\n179: - [ ] Add environment variable support\n180: - [ ] Document configuration options\n181: \n182: ### Logging\n183: - [ ] Implement structured logging\n184: - [ ] Add request/response logging\n185: - [ ] Add performance logging\n186: - [ ] Document log levels\n187: \n188: ### Type Checking\n189: - [ ] Run mypy on entire codebase\n190: - [ ] Fix any type errors\n191: - [ ] Add type stubs if needed\n192: - [ ] Configure mypy for strict mode\n193: \n194: ### Code Quality\n195: - [ ] Run black formatter\n196: - [ ] Run flake8 linter\n197: - [ ] Fix any linting issues\n198: - [ ] Add pre-commit hooks\n199: \n200: ### CI/CD\n201: - [ ] Set up GitHub Actions\n202: - [ ] Add linting step\n203: - [ ] Add type checking step\n204: - [ ] Add unit test step\n205: - [ ] Add integration test step\n206: - [ ] Add code coverage reporting\n\n(End of file - total 206 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Implementation Tasks\n\n## Phase 1: Core Infrastructure (Week 1-2)\n\n### 1.1 Project Setup\n- [ ] Create package directory structure\n- [ ] Set up pyproject.toml with dependencies\n- [ ] Configure development dependencies (pytest, mypy, black, etc.)\n- [ ] Create __init__.py files\n- [ ] Set up test directory structure\n\n### 1.2 Base HTTP Client\n- [ ] Implement base HTTP client class\n- [ ] Add authentication handling (API key in headers)\n- [ ] Implement retry logic with exponential backoff\n- [ ] Add timeout configuration\n- [ ] Implement error handling and response parsing\n- [ ] Add logging setup\n\n### 1.3 Data Models","truncated":false,