{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878266836,"sessionID":"ses_2856a97e0ffey48D6qOMQnb0po","part":{"id":"prt_d7a97db8d001UduE4e09u3eoU5","messageID":"msg_d7a965815001v5t6um2bz4Yz4a","sessionID":"ses_2856a97e0ffey48D6qOMQnb0po","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-ec181a0a22bf4b39bce8cca02aef3ae2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-028 Implementation Plan\n\n**Feature:** AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n**Goal:** Implement the AgentRuntimeClient in the AgentCube Python SDK, providing a streamlined interface for invoking agent runtime workloads through the Router service with proper session management.\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- AgentRuntimeClient provides high-level API for agent runtime interactions\n- Session ID is bootstrapped from Router or reused from existing session\n- Context manager support ensures proper resource cleanup\n- Invoke method handles HTTP communication via Router with proper timeout configuration\n- Connection pooling is implemented via requests.Session\n- Error handling includes session validation and HTTP error propagation\n- Unit tests achieve >80% code coverage\n- Integration tests work with real Router service\n**Architecture:** Python SDK client with AgentRuntimeClient (main API) and AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (HTTP layer), following context manager pattern for resource cleanup.\n**Tech Stack:** Python 3.10+, requests ^2.31.0\n**Frontend validation:** No\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Verify AgentRuntimeClient class structure\n\n**Files:**\n- Verify: `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n- Verify: `agentcube/__init__.py`\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\n```python\n# tests/test_agent_runtime_client_structure.py\nimport pytest\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n\ndef test_agent_runtime_client_has_required_methods():\n    \"\"\"Verify AgentRuntimeClient has all required public methods.\"\"\"\n    required_methods = [\n        \"__init__\",\n        \"__enter__\",\n        \"__exit__\",\n        \"invoke\",\n        \"close\",\n    ]\n\n    for method_name in required_methods:\n        assert hasattr(AgentRuntimeClient, method_name), f\"AgentRuntimeClient missing method: {method_name}\"\n\n\ndef test_agent_runtime_client_has_required_attributes():\n    \"\"\"Verify AgentRuntimeClient has all required instance attributes.\"\"\"\n    with pytest.mock.patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"):\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n        )\n\n    required_attributes = [\n        \"agent_name\",\n        \"namespace\",\n        \"timeout\",\n        \"connect_timeout\",\n        \"logger\",\n        \"router_url\",\n        \"session_id\",\n        \"dp_client\",\n        \"verbose\",\n    ]\n\n    for attr in required_attributes:\n        assert hasattr(client, attr), f\"AgentRuntimeClient missing attribute: {attr}\"\n\n    client.close()\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `python -m pytest tests/test_agent_runtime_client_structure.py -v`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 3: Verify AgentRuntimeClient is exported**\n\n```python\n# tests/test_public_api.py\nimport agentcube\n\n\ndef test_agent_runtime_client_exported():\n    \"\"\"Verify AgentRuntimeClient is exported from agentcube package.\"\"\"\n    assert hasattr(agentcube, \"AgentRuntimeClient\")\n    assert \"AgentRuntimeClient\" in agentcube.__all__\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `python -m pytest tests/test_public_api.py -v`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add tests/test_agent_runtime_client_structure.py tests/test_public_api.py\ngit commit -m \"test(ar-028): verify AgentRuntimeClient class structure\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Verify AgentRuntimeClient initialization with all parameters\n\n**Files:**\n- Verify: `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n- Modify: `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py`\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\n```python\n# tests/test_agent_runtime_client_initialization.py\nimport os\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nimport pytest\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n\ndef test_initialization_with_all_parameters():\n    \"\"\"Test AgentRuntimeClient initialization with all parameters.\"\"\"\n    with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n        mock_dp_instance = mock_dp.return_value\n        mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"test-session\"\n\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n            namespace=\"production\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            verbose=True,\n            session_id=\"existing-session\",\n            timeout=180,\n            connect_timeout=10.0,\n        )\n\n        assert client.agent_name == \"my-agent\"\n        assert client.namespace == \"production\"\n        assert client.router_url == \"http://router:8080\"\n        assert client.verbose is True\n        assert client.session_id == \"existing-session\"\n        assert client.timeout == 180\n        assert client.connect_timeout == 10.0\n\n        # Verify bootstrap_session_id was NOT called when session_id is provided\n        mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.assert_not_called()\n\n        client.close()\n\n\ndef test_initialization_defaults():\n    \"\"\"Test AgentRuntimeClient initialization with default values.\"\"\"\n    with patch.dict(os.environ, {\"ROUTER_URL\": \"http://router:8080\"}):\n        with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n            mock_dp_instance = mock_dp.return_value\n            mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"test-session\"\n\n            client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\")\n\n            assert client.agent_name == \"my-agent\"\n            assert client.namespace == \"default\"\n            assert client.router_url == \"http://router:8080\"\n            assert client.verbose is False\n            assert client.timeout == 120\n            assert client.connect_timeout == 5.0\n\n            # Verify bootstrap_session_id was called when session_id is NOT provided\n            mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.assert_called_once()\n\n            client.close()\n\n\ndef test_initialization_without_router_url_and_env():\n    \"\"\"Test AgentRuntimeClient initialization without router_url or env var.\"\"\"\n    with patch.dict(os.environ, {}, clear=True):\n        with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n            mock_dp_instance = mock_dp.return_value\n            mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"test-session\"\n\n            client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\")\n\n            assert client.router_url == \"\"\n            assert client.logger.warning.called\n\n            client.close()\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `python -m pytest tests/test_agent_runtime_client_initialization.py -v`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 3: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add tests/test_agent_runtime_client_initialization.py\ngit commit -m \"test(ar-028): verify AgentRuntimeClient initialization\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Verify AgentRuntimeClient context manager support\n\n**Files:**\n- Verify: `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n- Modify: `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py`\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\n```python\n# tests/test_agent_runtime_client_context_manager.py\nimport pytest\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n\ndef test_context_manager_enter_returns_self():\n    \"\"\"Test __enter__ returns self.\"\"\"\n    with pytest.mock.patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"):\n        with AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\") as client:\n            assert isinstance(client, AgentRuntimeClient)\n\n\ndef test_context_manager_exit_calls_close():\n    \"\"\"Test __exit__ calls close method.\"\"\"\n    with pytest.mock.patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"):\n        with pytest.mock.patch.object(AgentRuntimeClient, \"close\") as mock_close:\n            with AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\"):\n                pass\n\n            mock_close.assert_called_once()\n\n\ndef test_context_manager_exit_calls_close_on_exception():\n    \"\"\"Test __exit__ calls close method even when exception occurs.\"\"\"\n    with pytest.mock.patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"):\n        with pytest.mock.patch.object(AgentRuntimeClient, \"close\") as mock_close:\n            with pytest.raises(ValueError):\n                with AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\"):\n                    raise ValueError(\"Test error\")\n\n            mock_close.assert_called_once()\n\n\ndef test_close_is_idempotent():\n    \"\"\"Test close can be called multiple times without error.\"\"\"\n    with pytest.mock.patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"):\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\")\n\n        # First close\n        client.close()\n\n        # Second close should not raise\n        client.close()\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `python -m pytest tests/test_agent_runtime_client_context_manager.py -v`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 3: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add tests/test_agent_runtime_client_context_manager.py\ngit commit -m \"test(ar-028): verify AgentRuntimeClient context manager support\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Verify AgentRuntimeClient invoke method\n\n**Files:**\n- Verify: `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n- Modify: `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py`\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\n```python\n# tests/test_agent_runtime_client_invoke.py\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import MagicMock, patch\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n\ndef test_invoke_success():\n    \"\"\"Test invoke method with successful response.\"\"\"\n    with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n        mock_dp_instance = mock_dp.return_value\n        mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"test-session-id\"\n\n        mock_response = MagicMock()\n        mock_response.json.return_value = {\"result\": \"success\", \"data\": \"test\"}\n        mock_dp_instance.invoke.return_value = mock_response\n\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\")\n\n        payload = {\"query\": \"test query\"}\n        result = client.invoke(payload)\n\n        assert result == {\"result\": \"success\", \"data\": \"test\"}\n        mock_dp_instance.invoke.assert_called_once_with(\n            \"test-session-id\", payload, timeout=None\n        )\n\n        client.close()\n\n\ndef test_invoke_with_custom_timeout():\n    \"\"\"Test invoke method with custom timeout.\"\"\"\n    with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n        mock_dp_instance = mock_dp.return_value\n        mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"test-session-id\"\n\n        mock_response = MagicMock()\n        mock_response.json.return_value = {\"result\": \"success\"}\n        mock_dp_instance.invoke.return_value = mock_response\n\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\")\n\n        payload = {\"query\": \"test query\"}\n        result = client.invoke(payload, timeout=60.0)\n\n        assert result == {\"result\": \"success\"}\n        mock_dp_instance.invoke.assert_called_once_with(\n            \"test-session-id\", payload, timeout=60.0\n        )\n\n        client.close()\n\n\ndef test_invoke_without_session_id_raises_error():\n    \"\"\"Test invoke raises ValueError when session_id is not initialized.\"\"\"\n    with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n        mock_dp_instance = mock_dp.return_value\n        mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = None\n\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\")\n        client.session_id = None\n\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\"):\n            client.invoke({\"query\": \"test\"})\n\n        client.close()\n\n\ndef test_invoke_with_various_payloads():\n    \"\"\"Test invoke with various payload types.\"\"\"\n    with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n        mock_dp_instance = mock_dp.return_value\n        mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"test-session-id\"\n\n        mock_response = MagicMock()\n        mock_response.json.return_value = {\"result\": \"ok\"}\n        mock_dp_instance.invoke.return_value = mock_response\n\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\")\n\n        # Test with dict\n        result1 = client.invoke({\"key\": \"value\"})\n        assert result1 == {\"result\": \"ok\"}\n\n        # Test with nested dict\n        result2 = client.invoke({\"nested\": {\"key\": \"value\"}})\n        assert result2 == {\"result\": \"ok\"}\n\n        # Test with array\n        result3 = client.invoke({\"items\": [1, 2, 3]})\n        assert result3 == {\"result\": \"ok\"}\n\n        client.close()\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `python -m pytest tests/test_agent_runtime_client_invoke.py -v`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 3: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add tests/test_agent_runtime_client_invoke.py\ngit commit -m \"test(ar-028): verify AgentRuntimeClient invoke method\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Verify AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient implementation\n\n**Files:**\n- Verify: `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n- Create: `tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\n```python\n# tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import MagicMock, patch\nfrom agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n\ndef test_data_plane_client_initialization():\n    \"\"\"Test AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient initialization.\"\"\"\n    client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n        router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n        namespace=\"production\",\n        agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n        timeout=180,\n        connect_timeout=10.0,\n        pool_connections=20,\n        pool_maxsize=20,\n    )\n\n    assert client.router_url == \"http://router:8080\"\n    assert client.namespace == \"production\"\n    assert client.agent_name == \"test-agent\"\n    assert client.timeout == 180\n    assert client.connect_timeout == 10.0\n    assert client.base_url == \"http://router:8080/v1/namespaces/production/agent-runtimes/test-agent/invocations/\"\n\n    client.close()\n\n\ndef test_bootstrap_session_id_success():\n    \"\"\"Test bootstrap_session_id returns session ID from header.\"\"\"\n    with patch(\"agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane.create_session\") as mock_create:\n        mock_session = MagicMock()\n        mock_response = MagicMock()\n        mock_response.headers = {\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"test-session-123\"}\n        mock_session.get.return_value = mock_response\n        mock_create.return_value = mock_session\n\n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n        )\n\n        session_id = client.bootstrap_session_id()\n\n        assert session_id == \"test-session-123\"\n        mock_session.get.assert_called_once_with(\n            client.base_url,\n            timeout=(5.0, 120)\n        )\n\n        client.close()\n\n\ndef test_bootstrap_session_id_missing_header_raises_error():\n    \"\"\"Test bootstrap_session_id raises ValueError when header is missing.\"\"\"\n    with patch(\"agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane.create_session\") as mock_create:\n        mock_session = MagicMock()\n        mock_response = MagicMock()\n        mock_response.headers = {}\n        mock_session.get.return_value = mock_response\n        mock_create.return_value = mock_session\n\n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n        )\n\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Missing required response header\"):\n            client.bootstrap_session_id()\n\n        client.close()\n\n\ndef test_invoke_success():\n    \"\"\"Test invoke method with successful response.\"\"\"\n    with patch(\"agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane.create_session\") as mock_create:\n        mock_session = MagicMock()\n        mock_response = MagicMock()\n        mock_response.json.return_value = {\"result\": \"success\"}\n        mock_session.post.return_value = mock_response\n        mock_create.return_value = mock_session\n\n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n        )\n\n        payload = {\"query\": \"test\"}\n        response = client.invoke(\"session-123\", payload)\n\n        assert response.json() == {\"result\": \"success\"}\n        mock_session.post.assert_called_once_with(\n            client.base_url,\n            json=payload,\n            headers={\n                \"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"session-123\",\n                \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n            },\n            timeout=(5.0, 120)\n        )\n\n        client.close()\n\n\ndef test_invoke_with_custom_timeout():\n    \"\"\"Test invoke method with custom timeout.\"\"\"\n    with patch(\"agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane.create_session\") as mock_create:\n        mock_session = MagicMock()\n        mock_response = MagicMock()\n        mock_response.json.return_value = {\"result\": \"success\"}\n        mock_session.post.return_value = mock_response\n        mock_create.return_value = mock_session\n\n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n        )\n\n        payload = {\"query\": \"test\"}\n        response = client.invoke(\"session-123\", payload, timeout=60.0)\n\n        assert response.json() == {\"result\": \"success\"}\n        mock_session.post.assert_called_once_with(\n            client.base_url,\n            json=payload,\n            headers={\n                \"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"session-123\",\n                \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n            },\n            timeout=(5.0, 60.0)  # Custom read timeout\n        )\n\n        client.close()\n\n\ndef test_session_header_constant():\n    \"\"\"Test SESSION_HEADER constant.\"\"\"\n    assert AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.SESSION_HEADER == \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `python -m pytest tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py -v`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 3: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py\ngit commit -m \"test(ar-028): verify AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient implementation\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Verify HTTP session creation and connection pooling\n\n**Files:**\n- Verify: `agentcube/utils/http.py`\n- Create: `tests/test_http_utils.py`\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\n```python\n# tests/test_http_utils.py\nimport pytest\nimport requests\nfrom requests.adapters import HTTPAdapter\nfrom agentcube.utils import create_session\n\n\ndef test_create_session_default_parameters():\n    \"\"\"Test create_session with default parameters.\"\"\"\n    session = create_session()\n\n    assert isinstance(session, req